The paper discusses a framework for turn-based interaction between human users and AI agents designed to support human creativity. This involves studying co-creative AI systems, which are likely to fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the design space of co-creative systems, which could fall under the sub-categories of Computational Creativity (cs.CC) and Cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper also discusses the results of human subject studies, which could fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
